<http://www.example.org/elearning-ontology> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology> .
<http://www.example.org/elearning-ontology> <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/creator> "Fatma Alsaghir (220315105)" .
<http://www.example.org/elearning-ontology> <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/date> "2026-05-12" .
<http://www.example.org/elearning-ontology> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An OWL ontology modelling the core concepts of an e-learning system,\nincluding courses, modules, assignments, student submissions, grades,\nfeedback, learning objectives, and instructor relationships. Developed\nas part of a Knowledge Engineering course project using Protégé and\nvalidated with the HermiT reasoner."@en .
<http://www.example.org/elearning-ontology> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "E-Learning Ontology"@en .
<http://www.example.org/elearning-ontology> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo> "2.0" .
